        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> One of the things that has always bothered me is that other people in a fight dont know how much damage my DoTs do.  I would like to see at the end of a DoT ( or even per tick) a message that tells how much damage the Dot did.  For example : Soandso's blood stabilizes, and has taken 780 damage.  I feel one reason why necro's arent thought of as a damage dealing class by many people is they don't see some hard damage number's.  When a wizard crits everyone sees it. We all get to see how much damage a melee person does.</P><P>I figure while they are making changes then they can do this.</P><P><BR>Baron Daryth Shadowspawn<BR>Warlock of Stormhammer</P><P><BR>"Its not your soul, you were just holding it for me."</font></td>

