        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         If a group has concerns about your dmg then one of two things are the problem:</P><P>1) They are still new and do not realise how mana efficient dot's are can be. They just haven't been exposed to enough of the game. Very common in the lower levels...sadly it still occurs in the upper levels.</P><P>2) We're not all about dmg and they have yet to discover that. we can fill in for almost any spot in a group if need be. We may not be the best, but we get the job done. Educate them to the wide array of tools you have at your disposal.</P><P>It doesn't matter who does the dmg. It doesn't matter who healed, who did the crowd control or who ate the muffins. What matters is that when you leave their group and they see the void you left behind by leaving that they then understand what we do.</P><P>I deal dmg. I heal dmg. I prevent dmg. In an exp group (discounting ae groups of course..whole different beast there) I can fulfil any of those 3 key roles. I have the tools to perform them well. Perhaps I couldn't heal as easily as a cleric, but the tank didn't die and we never had to stop because I  had run low on mana. Perhaps I couldn't do crowd control as beautifuly as the enchanter, but did the casters ever take more then a single hit? Did the tank ever have more than once mob he had to tank at a time? Perhaps I didn't get a number flash across the screen saying "Charbonez has scored a critical hit!" but wasn't jabober staggering as he sucked the life from the next victim? Didn't the mob clutch it's chest and appear a bit weaker? </P><P>Put the numbers up there or don't, but if you do then please leave it for after the last tick and/or when it is dispelled/canceled. You'd be amazed what 2-3 extra lines of spam comming from 3 different people or more every 6 seconds can do to lag. Remember EC when people would turn off the auction channel before even zoneing into EC? </P><P>We aren't thought of as a damage dealing class by the ignorant who have yet to get a clue. The only time we ever suffer and are not able to do acceptable dmg is on large raids with multiple necros or mobs that have high resists. Even then we'll most likely have a dot that will go through due to our wide array of options.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_blank">Charbonez Soulmark</a><BR>Duzzil Ro<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
